# Docker build context excludes. Both images (deploy/Dockerfile.api and
# deploy/Dockerfile.web) use the REPO ROOT as their build context, so
# everything here is sent to the daemon on every build unless excluded.
#
# ⚠️ This file's absence was a real prod outage: the compose bind mounts put
# Postgres's data directory at deploy/pg-data/, owned by the container's
# postgres uid with 0700 perms. The build-context sender runs as the runner
# user, can't read it, and the whole build dies with
#   "error from sender: open .../deploy/pg-data: permission denied"
# Every self-hosted-runner deploy failed this way. Excluding the runtime data
# dirs fixes that AND stops shipping an entire database to the daemon on
# every build.
#
# NOTE: .gitignore does NOT apply to Docker build contexts — the two lists
# have to be maintained separately. Keep the runtime/data entries below in
# sync with .gitignore's "runtime / local data" block.

# runtime / local data — never belongs in an image, and pg-data is unreadable
pg-data/
deploy/pg-data/
minio-data/
deploy/minio-data/
deploy/caddy-data/
deploy/caddy-config/
tmp/
server/tmp/
*.log

# secrets — must never enter a build context, let alone a layer
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# dependencies + build output: images run their own npm install and build,
# so shipping these only slows the context upload and risks host/container
# native-binary mismatches (sharp, @node-rs/argon2).
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
dist/
build/
app/dev-dist/
*.tsbuildinfo

# vcs / CI / editor / docs — not needed by any build stage
.git/
.github/
.playwright-mcp/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
docs/

# NOTE: deploy/ itself is deliberately NOT excluded — Dockerfile.web does
# `COPY deploy/Caddyfile /etc/caddy/Caddyfile`, and Dockerfile.api needs
# nothing from it but is happy either way. Only the data dirs above are cut.
